Photo: Bexar County Sheriff's Office Image 32 of 32 Texas man with substance on his face arrested, tells police: ‘I am the law' 1 / 32 Back to Gallery A man with a dark substance on his face was arrested Monday in Denton on non-alcohol public intoxication and drug paraphernalia charges.
When police asked him for his name, he repeatedly said: "I am the law!" and "I know the law, I am the law," according to a Denton Police Department probable cause affidavit. He was later identified as Joseph Augustini, 25.
Officers were called to the scene at 11 a.m., after people reported seeing him darting in and out of traffic on the 200 block of East McKinney Street near the Denton Square.
When they arrived, he told them to remove their guns or it wouldn't be a "fair fight" and continued "rambling random answers."
STRANGE ARREST: Elderly couple set house on fire to lure police into ambush
The affidavit reports that Augustini said the officer was in his "circle" and pointed at a drawing of a star on his knee.
He then began repeating: "I want the truth, the whole truth and nothing but the truth."
Augustini reportedly told police that he was suicidal, saying that he wanted to go in a "f**king cell and kill" himself.
Denton Police Department administrator Sean Kirk said are still unsure of what the substance on his face was. The affidavit refers to it as "makeup" and "ink," that was also used to draw a spider web on the "rest of his body."
He had a "clear glass pipe" with residue that tested positive for amphetamines.
